            , the watchman. confirmed the above account.</p>
               <p>The prisoner, in his defence, said he had been at work for one Hodges; had got drunk; and went to sleep in the house, about four o'clock in the afternoon, and knew nothing of the lead.</p>
               <p>He called no witnesses to his character.</p>
